ZH: 他对我说的是一个善意的谎言。
EN: He told me a white lie.

ZH: 她的解释只是一个善意的谎言。
EN: Her explanation was just a well-meaning lie.

ZH: 我不得不说一些善意的谎言来保护他的感情。
EN: I had to tell some well-intentioned lies to protect his feelings.

ZH: 她编造了一个善意的谎言来安慰受伤的朋友。
EN: She fabricated a kind lie to comfort her friend who was hurt.

ZH: 有时候，我们需要说一些善意的谎言来维持和谐的关系。
EN: Sometimes, we need to tell some kind lies to maintain harmonious relationships.

ZH: 在某些情况下，善意的谎言可以避免冲突。
EN: In certain situations, well-intentioned lies can avoid conflicts.

ZH: 那个孩子只是告诉了一个善意的谎言，让他妈妈高兴。
EN: The child just told a little white lie to make his mom happy.

ZH: 她对老板撒了一个善意的谎言来请假。
EN: She told a well-meant lie to her boss to take a day off.

