EN: She made up a kind lie to avoid hurting her parents' feelings.

ZH: 在某些情况下，善意的谎言可以成为一个有效的交际工具。
EN: In certain situations, well-intentioned lies can serve as an effective social tool.

ZH: 有时候，我们只能用善意的谎言来安慰他人。
EN: Sometimes, we can only comfort others with well-meant lies.

ZH: 她对他的谎言并不完全是恶意的，有些也是善意的谎言。
EN: Her lies to him were not entirely malicious, some were white lies as well.

ZH: 当你不想伤害别人时，有时候你需要借助一些善意的谎言。
EN: When you don't want to hurt someone, sometimes you need to resort to well-intentioned lies.

ZH: 善意的谎言可能会暂时掩盖真相，但最终还是会被揭穿。
EN: Well-meaning lies may temporarily conceal the truth, but they will eventually be exposed.

ZH: 有时候，善意的谎言可以给人们带来一些安慰和欢乐。
EN: Sometimes, well-intentioned lies can bring comfort and joy to people.

